examples.name: GenomePaint
examples.blurb: Explore coding and non-coding variants in cancer

ppcalls.label: Launch an Official Dataset
ppcalls.message: This is an example of how to launch one of the official datasets available in ProteinPaint.

ppcalls.label: Customize with a Mds JSON
ppcalls.message: This example of a mdsjson demostrates how to separate samples into subgroups. The json file may available from the server and accessed via the mdsjsonfile key or available from a URL and accessed via the mdsjsonurl key.

arrowButtons.name: Data Processing
arrowButtons.message: Download the data and data processing scripts from the Download Data & Processing Pipeline link. Please use the Data Processing Docs for instructions

ppcalls.label: BED3
ppcalls.message: The bare minimum for the JSON BED track is a three column tab-delimited file with the chromosome, start position, and stop position. Below is example of the barebone rendering of the data.

ppcalls.label: URL Linkout
ppcalls.message: Click on a SNP item to see details on the dbSNP website.

ppcalls.label: Hide item names
ppcalls.message: In this example, the gene name is removed. To add the gene name, navigate to the farthest left-hand side of the track, and click on CONFIG. Uncheck 'Hide item names' and the gene symbol will reappear.

ppcalls.label: Show item by name
ppcalls.message:
To single out genes of interest, click CONFIG on the farthest left-hand side of the track. Enter the isoform name(s) under 'Show items by names' and click .

In this example, only MYC and PVT1 are shown. Delete one of the names and uncheck 'Show items by names' to see the differences in the track display.

ppcalls.label: Color exons
ppcalls.message:
In the bedj file JSON object, create an "exon2color" array with {"color": "XX", "start": ##, "stop": ##} objects. For instance, this array defines the exon colors for this example.

"exon2color": [{"color": "red", "start": 129146958, "stop": 129147048},...]

examples.name: Expression rank
examples.blurb: Against all samples from a cohort

ppcalls.label: GDC API (GENCODE)
ppcalls.message:
To view a different gene from the GDC dataset:
  • Scroll to the top of the page. Select 'human hg38' from the dropdown menu in the header.
  • Start typing the gene into the search bar. A vertical menu of gene options will appear. Click the appropriate option or hit enter.
  • The protein view of the gene will appear. Click on
    GDC
    in the toolbar.

ppcalls.label: GDC API (RefSeq)
ppcalls.message:
To view a different gene from the GDC dataset:
  • Scroll to the top of the page. Select 'human hg38' from the dropdown menu in the header.
  • Start typing the gene into the search bar. A vertical menu of gene options will appear. Click the appropriate option or hit enter.
  • The protein view of the gene will appear. Click on
    GDC
    in the toolbar.

sandbox.intro:
To view the facet table:

  • Click on the in the genome browser toolbar
  • A button appears under FACET. Click on
  • Launch tracks by clicking on individual cells, samples (row labels), or assays (column labels).
